	     <br clear="all" /><small>Posted @ Sat, Apr 17th 5:54 AM 2004</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=310441"><span id=" ">Vorpledge</span></a><br /><span id="notbold">6 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score:</span> Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>&nbsp;&nbsp; IMO this Item is best for necros. The Sta and Regen ability cant be beat with how much HP they go through. there are better suited robes for the other caster classes if you are in VT. Emp Robe, Robe of Luring Shadows and Robe of Secrets. True the Preservation is good for chanters who buff alot, but in PoP today the buffs last so long with AAs and such that this isnt all that great. Plus you almost never see a good chanter run out of mana from casting rune again and again. Best go for Robe of Luring Shadows for it's effect to help with Mezzes and such, Robe of Secrets for the massive FT on one item and better stats, or Emp robe for the better stats and the 8 extra mana effect it gives. <br/>   Mages and Wizards? Not a chance! like I said .. look at the above robes and consider them first!<br/>  It IS a nice robe that any class can benifit in some way, though please consider what class could use it best on your raids when your throw in your DKP. <br/></p>&nbsp;<br /><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br />Umpy<br/>60 Shaman<br/>Shadowsong</td></tr>
